If you call `document.querySelector(selector)` and your *selector* variable is this just a name:  `const selector = 'spacer-over-cta';`  you have to add a *dot* in front of the selector! Like this: `document.querySelector('.'+ selector)` .

The *source map* is a different thing and has nothing to do with the observer. Maybe some external library files you have in your bundle. Or added by a pre-compiler like sass, then change the compiler config. Check your files if there is in the last line, something like this and remove it.

JS `//# sourceMappingURL=path/to/file.js.map`
 CSS `/*# sourceMappingURL=path/to/file.css.map */`
Thanks so much Mitja! I'm going to try it and see if it makes a difference! Thanks for all of your help you both!
